🎯 Aim
To perform an advanced Power Query transformation by combining quarterly files from a folder and applying data standardization, unpivoting, de-duplication, type correction, and data quality validation.
🧭 Algorithm (12 Points)
1.	Open Excel / Power BI and select Get Data → From Folder.
2.	Choose the folder containing Mar_Sales and Apr_Sales files.
3.	Use Combine & Transform to append the files.
4.	Standardize column names into lowercase meaningful names.
5.	Apply Trim and Clean on city column to remove spaces.
6.	Assign correct data types for all columns.
7.	Select product columns and perform Unpivot Columns.
8.	Rename Attribute and Value columns to product and quantity.
9.	Remove duplicate records based on order_id.
10.	Verify no missing or invalid quantity values.
11.	Create a duplicate query and perform Group By for row count.
12.	Create and load a Data Quality Summary table.

